article.description: Stanley Davis scored 28 points and grabbed 11 rebounds and Morgan State beat Division II Chestnut Hill College 96-72 on Monday in the first meeting of the teams.
article.headline: Morgan State tops Chestnut Hill College 96-72 behind Davis
article.linkText: Morgan State tops Chestnut Hill College 96-72 behind Davis
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Stanley Davis scored 28 points and grabbed 11 rebounds and Morgan State beat Division II Chestnut Hill College 96-72 on Monday in the first meeting of the teams. Sherwyn Devonish-Prince added 16 points and Troy Baxter Jr. had 14 points and nine rebounds for the Bears (5-8), who shot 68% from the field in the first half and led 53-26 at halftime. Isaiah Burke added 10 points. Davis and Devonish-Prince combined for 11 points in the Bears' opening 16-3 run. Morgan State finished shooting 54%, outrebounded the Griffins 47-23 and outscored them 52-30 in the paint. James Rider and Trevonn Pitts scored 15 points apiece for the Griffins (0-10). Amir Warrick added 14 points and Scottie Spann had 13. Morgan State plays a Loyola Marymount next Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25
